syntax_errors.question: What is the term description, whether the term is current or not, total number of types of TIP subjects offered and materials needed, the minimum and maximum number of enrolled students, the total number of schools offering subjects, and the total number of records for each term code?

runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    a.TERM_DESCRIPTION,
    a.IS_CURRENT_TERM,
    COUNT(DISTINCT s.TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY) AS total_tip_subjects_offered,
    COUNT(DISTINCT d.TIP_MATERIAL_KEY) AS total_materials_needed,
    MIN(s.NUM_ENROLLED_STUDENTS) AS min_enrolled_students,
    MAX(s.NUM_ENROLLED_STUDENTS) AS max_enrolled_students,
    COUNT(DISTINCT s.OFFER_SCHOOL_NAME) AS total_schools_offering_subjects,
    COUNT(*) AS total_records
FROM 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS_ALL a
LEFT JOIN 
    TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED s ON a.TERM_CODE = s.TERM_CODE
LEFT JOIN 
    TIP_DETAIL d ON a.TERM_CODE = d.TERM_CODE
GROUP BY 
    a.TERM_CODE, a.TERM_DESCRIPTION, a.IS_CURRENT_TERM;

syntax_errors.question: For each term code, list the term description, attribute desciption, department name, school name, and the number of subjects in the area of humanities, arts and social sciences.

runs.predicted_sql:

    a.TERM_CODE,
    a.TERM_DESCRIPTION,
    c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE_DESC,
    d.DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    d.SCHOOL_NAME,
    COUNT(*) AS NUM_SUBJECTS
FROM 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS_ALL a
JOIN 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED b ON a.TERM_CODE = b.TERM_CODE
JOIN 
    CIS_HASS_ATTRIBUTE c ON FIND_IN_SET(c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE, b.HASS_ATTRIBUTE) > 0

syntax_errors.question: List building names, their height, street address, city, state, postal code, their gross and assignable square footage, the smallest and largest floor level and the total area of all rooms for each building key.

runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    b.BUILDING_NAME,
    fb.BUILDING_HEIGHT,
    fba.STREET_NUMBER || ' ' || fba.STREET_NAME || ' ' || fba.STREET_SUFFIX AS STREET_ADDRESS,
    fba.CITY,
    fba.STATE,
    fba.POSTAL_CODE,
    b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    MIN(ff.FLOOR) AS SMALLEST_FLOOR_LEVEL,
    MAX(ff.FLOOR) AS LARGEST_FLOOR_LEVEL,
    SUM(fr.AREA) AS TOTAL_ROOM_AREA
FROM 
    BUILDINGS b
JOIN 
    FAC_BUILDING_ADDRESS fba ON b.BUILDING_KEY = fba.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_FLOOR ff ON b.BUILDING_KEY = ff.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_ROOMS fr ON b.BUILDING_KEY = fr.BUILDING_KEY
GROUP BY 
    b.BUILDING_KEY, b.BUILDING_NAME, fb.BUILDING_HEIGHT, fba.STREET_NUMBER, fba.STREET_NAME, fba.STREET_SUFFIX, fba.CITY, fba.STATE, fba.POSTAL_CODE, b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE, b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE;

    b.BUILDING_NAME,
    fb.BUILDING_HEIGHT,
    CONCAT(fba.STREET_NUMBER, ' ', fba.STREET_NAME, ' ', fba.STREET_SUFFIX) AS STREET_ADDRESS,

    fba.STATE,
    fba.POSTAL_CODE,
    b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,

syntax_errors.question: For email lists with names starting with C (case insensitive) and containing faculty who teach courses in the summer in financial aid years after 2001, provide the name of the list, the number of people in the list, and the number of faculty in the list.

runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS total_members,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN ccso.SUMMER_INSTRUCTORS IS NOT NULL THEN mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER END) AS faculty_members
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    EMPLOYEE_DIRECTORY ed ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = ed.MIT_ID
JOIN 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED ccso ON ed.FULL_NAME = ccso.SUMMER_INSTRUCTORS
JOIN 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS at ON ccso.TERM_CODE = at.TERM_CODE
WHERE 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME LIKE 'C%' 
    AND at.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR > '2001'
    AND ccso.IS_OFFERED_SUMMER_TERM = 'Y'
GROUP BY 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME;

SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS total_members,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN ccso.SUMMER_INSTRUCTORS IS NOT NULL THEN mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER END) AS faculty_count
FROM

SELECT

    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN ccso.SUMMER_INSTRUCTORS IS NOT NULL THEN mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER END) AS faculty_count

    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID) AS faculty_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT c.SUBJECT_ID) AS course_count
FROM 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED c
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON c.RESPONSIBLE_FACULTY_MIT_ID = mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID

syntax_errors.question: Give the count of mailing lists with names starting with B that include members from the Electrical Engineering and Computer Science department, along with the name of the list starting with B that have the highest number of members from that department and the corresponding member count.

runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    COUNT(DISTINCT ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY) AS mailing_list_count,
    subquery.MOIRA_LIST_NAME AS list_with_max_members,
    subquery.max_member_count
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    SE_PERSON sp ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = sp.MIT_ID
JOIN 
    (SELECT 
        ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
        COUNT(*) AS max_member_count
     FROM 
        MOIRA_LIST ml
     JOIN 
        MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY

    FORMAT(AVG(CAST(r.AREA AS DECIMAL(10,2))), 0) AS 'Average Area per Floor',

syntax_errors.question: For each IAP category, list its name, number of unique sessions, total number of attendees, active period (in the format of 'beginning term code-end term code'), the most common sponsor name, and the most common session start time. Include a grand total row showing the total number of sessions and attendees across all categories in the format of ('TOTAL', number of sessions, number of attendees, null, null, null).

runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    COALESCE(c.IAP_CATEGORY_NAME, 'TOTAL') AS IAP_CATEGORY_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT d.IAP_SUBJECT_SESSION_KEY) AS UNIQUE_SESSIONS,
    SUM(d.MAX_ENROLLMENT) AS TOTAL_ATTENDEES,
    CASE 
        WHEN c.IAP_CATEGORY_NAME IS NOT NULL THEN CONCAT(MIN(d.TERM_CODE), '-', MAX(d.TERM_CODE))
        ELSE NULL
    END AS ACTIVE_PERIOD,
    CASE 
        WHEN c.IAP_CATEGORY_NAME IS NOT NULL THEN (
            SELECT s.SPONSOR_NAME
            FROM IAP_SUBJECT_DETAIL d2
            JOIN IAP_SUBJECT_SPONSOR s ON d2.IAP_SUBJECT_SPONSOR_KEY = s.IAP_SUBJECT_SPONSOR_KEY
            WHERE d2.IAP_SUBJECT_CATEGORY_KEY = c.IAP_SUBJECT_CATEGORY_KEY
            GROUP BY s.SPONSOR_NAME
            ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
            LIMIT 1
        )
        ELSE NULL
    END AS MOST_COMMON_SPONSOR,
    CASE 
        WHEN c.IAP_CATEGORY_NAME IS NOT NULL THEN (
            SELECT ss.SESSION_START_TIME
            FROM IAP_SUBJECT_DETAIL d3
            JOIN IAP_SUBJECT_SESSION ss ON d3.IAP_SUBJECT_SESSION_KEY = ss.IAP_SUBJECT_SESSION_KEY
            WHERE d3.IAP_SUBJECT_CATEGORY_KEY = c.IAP_SUBJECT_CATEGORY_KEY
            GROUP BY ss.SESSION_START_TIME
            ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
            LIMIT 1
        )
        ELSE NULL
    END AS MOST_COMMON_START_TIME
FROM 
    IAP_SUBJECT_CATEGORY c
LEFT JOIN 
    IAP_SUBJECT_DETAIL d ON c.IAP_SUBJECT_CATEGORY_KEY = d.IAP_SUBJECT_CATEGORY_KEY
GROUP BY 
    c.IAP_CATEGORY_NAME WITH ROLLUP
HAVING 
    c.IAP_CATEGORY_NAME IS NOT NULL OR c.IAP_CATEGORY_NAME IS NULL
ORDER BY 
    c.IAP_CATEGORY_NAME;

runs.predicted_sql:
WITH BuildingDetails AS (

        SUM(ff.ASSIGNABLE_AREA) AS TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA,
        fb.NUM_OF_ROOMS,
        COUNT(DISTINCT fr.FCLT_ORGANIZATION_KEY) AS TOTAL_ORGANIZATIONS,
        fb.OWNERSHIP_TYPE
    FROM 
        FCLT_BUILDING fb
    LEFT JOIN 
        FCLT_BUILDING_ADDRESS fba ON fb.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY = fba.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY
    LEFT JOIN 
        FCLT_FLOOR ff ON fb.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY = ff.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY
    LEFT JOIN

inconsistent.question: For each department and material status, list the name of the department, the material status, the number of TIP materials associated with this department and status, the number of library materials associated with this department and status, the total number of TIP and library materials associated with this department and status.     COUNT(DISTINCT tm.TIP_MATERIAL_KEY) AS TIP_Material_Count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS Library_Material_Count,

    TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED tso
LEFT JOIN 
    TIP_DETAIL td ON tso.TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = td.TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
LEFT JOIN 
    TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS tms ON td.TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY = tms.TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY
LEFT JOIN 
    LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED lso ON tso.SUBJECT_ID = lso.SUBJECT_ID
LEFT JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrm ON lso.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = lrm.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
LEFT JOIN 
    LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS lms ON lrm.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY = lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY
GROUP BY 
    tso.OFFER_DEPT_NAME, tms.TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS, lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS

all_success.question: List all buildings with their names, building numbers, building height, street address, city, state, HR department name, assignable square footage, total and average square footage, ordered in descending order of assignable, total, and average square footage.

runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    b.BUILDING_NAME,
    b.BUILDING_NUMBER,
    fb.BUILDING_HEIGHT,
    fba.STREET_NUMBER || ' ' || fba.STREET_NAME || ' ' || fba.STREET_SUFFIX AS STREET_ADDRESS,
    fba.CITY,
    fba.STATE,
    fo.HR_DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE AS TOTAL_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    (b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE / NULLIF(b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE, 0)) AS AVERAGE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE
FROM 
    BUILDINGS b
JOIN 
    FAC_BUILDING fb ON b.BUILDING_NUMBER = fb.BUILDING_NUMBER
JOIN 
    FAC_BUILDING_ADDRESS fba ON b.BUILDING_KEY = fba.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_ROOMS fr ON b.BUILDING_KEY = fr.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_ORGANIZATION fo ON fr.ORGANIZATION_KEY = fo.ORGANIZATION_KEY
ORDER BY 
    b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE DESC,
    b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE DESC,
    (b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE / NULLIF(b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE, 0)) DESC;

    b.BUILDING_NAME,
    b.BUILDING_NUMBER,
    fb.BUILDING_HEIGHT,
    fba.STREET_NUMBER,
    fba.STREET_NAME,
    fba.CITY,
    fba.STATE,
    fo.HR_DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    (b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE + b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE) AS TOTAL_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    ((b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE + b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE) / 2) AS AVERAGE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE

all_success.question: For each financial aid year and academic year, list the number of fiscal periods, quarters, the start term date, the end term date, and number of distinct department-level term parameters.

runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    t.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR,
    t.ACADEMIC_YEAR,
    COUNT(DISTINCT tm.FISCAL_PERIOD) AS num_fiscal_periods,
    COUNT(DISTINCT tq.FY_QUARTER_CODE) AS num_quarters,
    MIN(at.TERM_START_DATE) AS start_term_date,
    MAX(at.TERM_END_DATE) AS end_term_date,
    COUNT(DISTINCT atp.TERM_PARAMETER) AS num_distinct_term_parameters
FROM 
    TIME_DAY t
LEFT JOIN 
    TIME_MONTH tm ON t.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR = tm.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR AND t.ACADEMIC_YEAR = tm.ACADEMIC_YEAR
LEFT JOIN 
    TIME_QUARTER tq ON t.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR = tq.FISCAL_YEAR
LEFT JOIN 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS at ON t.ACADEMIC_YEAR = at.ACADEMIC_YEAR
LEFT JOIN 
    ACADEMIC_TERM_PARAMETER atp ON at.TERM_CODE = atp.TERM_CODE
GROUP BY 
    t.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR, t.ACADEMIC_YEAR;

SELECT 
    t.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR,
    t.ACADEMIC_YEAR,

    FORMAT(room_count, 0) AS room_count,
    FORMAT(ROUND(total_area), 0) AS total_area,
    FORMAT(ROUND(total_area / room_count), 0) AS avg_area_per_room
FROM (
    SELECT 
        FLOOR_KEY,
        ORGANIZATION_NAME,
        room_count,
        total_area
    FROM 
        RoomDetails
    UNION ALL
    SELECT 
        FLOOR_KEY,
        ORGANIZATION_NAME,
        room_count,
        total_area
    FROM 
        FloorSubtotals
    UNION ALL
    SELECT 
        FLOOR_KEY,
        ORGANIZATION_NAME,
        room_count,
        total_area
    FROM 
        GrandTotal
) AS CombinedResults
ORDER BY 
    FLOOR_KEY IS NULL, FLOOR_KEY, ORGANIZATION_NAME IS NULL, ORGANIZATION_NAME;

WITH RoomDetails AS (
    SELECT 
        fr.FLOOR_KEY,
        fr.ORGANIZATION_NAME,
        COUNT(fr.ROOM) AS num_rooms,
        SUM(CAST(fr.AREA AS DECIMAL(10, 2))) AS total_area
    FROM 
        FAC_ROOMS fr
    JOIN 
        BUILDINGS b ON fr.BUILDING_KEY = b.BUILDING_KEY
    WHERE 
        b.BUILDING_NAME = 'Stata'
    GROUP BY 
        fr.FLOOR_KEY, fr.ORGANIZATION_NAME
),
FloorSubtotals AS (
    SELECT 
        FLOOR_KEY,
        NULL AS ORGANIZATION_NAME,
        SUM(num_rooms) AS num_rooms,
        SUM(total_area) AS total_area
    FROM 
        RoomDetails
    GROUP BY 
        FLOOR_KEY
),
GrandTotal AS (
    SELECT 
        NULL AS FLOOR_KEY,
        NULL AS ORGANIZATION_NAME,
        SUM(num_rooms) AS num_rooms,
        SUM(total_area) AS total_area
    FROM 
        RoomDetails
)
SELECT 
    CASE WHEN ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY rd.FLOOR_KEY ORDER BY rd.ORGANIZATION_NAME) = 1 THEN rd.FLOOR_KEY ELSE NULL END AS FLOOR_KEY,
    rd.ORGANIZATION_NAME,
    FORMAT(rd.num_rooms, 0) AS num_rooms,
    FORMAT(rd.total_area, 0) AS total_area,
    FORMAT(ROUND(rd.total_area / rd.num_rooms, 0), 0) AS avg_area
FROM 
    RoomDetails rd
UNION ALL
SELECT 
    NULL AS FLOOR_KEY,
    NULL AS ORGANIZATION_NAME,
    FORMAT(fs.num_rooms, 0) AS num_rooms,
    FORMAT(fs.total_area, 0) AS total_area,
    NULL AS avg_area
FROM 
    FloorSubtotals fs
UNION ALL
SELECT 
    NULL AS FLOOR_KEY,
    NULL AS ORGANIZATION_NAME,
    FORMAT(gt.num_rooms, 0) AS num_rooms,
    FORMAT(gt.total_area, 0) AS total_area,
    NULL AS avg_area
FROM 
    GrandTotal gt
ORDER BY 
    FLOOR_KEY, ORGANIZATION_NAME;

    c.CATEGORY_TITLE, c.VERSION, s.DEPARTMENT_NAME, s.SCHOOL_NAME, sc.COURSE_LEVEL;

all_runs.question: What is the total number of library materials, the minimum and maximum publication years, and the total number of materials status for each course name?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    lci.COURSE_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS total_library_materials,
    MIN(CAST(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR AS UNSIGNED)) AS min_publication_year,
    MAX(CAST(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR AS UNSIGNED)) AS max_publication_year,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrm.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY) AS total_material_status
FROM 
    LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR lci
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrmd ON lci.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY = lrmd.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG lrc ON lrmd.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY = lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS lms ON lrmd.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY = lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY
GROUP BY 
    lci.COURSE_NAME;

all_runs.question: What is the total number of library reserve materials, the minimum and maximum publication years, and the total number of enrolled students for each course instructor?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    lci.INSTRUCTOR_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS total_library_reserve_materials,
    MIN(CAST(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR AS UNSIGNED)) AS min_publication_year,
    MAX(CAST(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR AS UNSIGNED)) AS max_publication_year,
    SUM(lso.NUM_ENROLLED_STUDENTS) AS total_enrolled_students
FROM 
    LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR lci
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrm ON lci.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY = lrm.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG lrc ON lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY = lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED lso ON lrm.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = lso.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
GROUP BY 
    lci.INSTRUCTOR_NAME;

all_runs.question: What is the material status, term description, total number of courses and materials, occurences in departments and school, and the total number of instructors for each library material status code and term code?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_CODE,
    ata.TERM_DESCRIPTION,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lcid.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY) AS total_courses,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS total_materials,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lso.OFFER_DEPT_CODE) AS occurrences_in_departments,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lso.OFFER_SCHOOL_NAME) AS occurrences_in_schools,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lci.INSTRUCTOR_NAME) AS total_instructors
FROM 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrm
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS lms ON lrm.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY = lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY
JOIN 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS_ALL ata ON lrm.TERM_CODE = ata.TERM_CODE
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR lci ON lrm.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY = lci.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG lrc ON lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY = lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED lso ON lrm.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = lso.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
GROUP BY 
    lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_CODE, ata.TERM_DESCRIPTION;

all_runs.question: For each distinct mailing list containing more than 1000 people and with a name starting with A (case insensitive), provide its name, whether it is a mailing list, whether it is a moira group, whether it is a NFS group, the owner of the mailing list, and the number of people in the list.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST,
    ml.IS_MOIRA_GROUP,
    ml.IS_NFS_GROUP,
    mo.OWNER,
    COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS number_of_people
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_OWNER mo ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY = mo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
WHERE 
    ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
    AND ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME LIKE 'A%'
GROUP BY 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME, ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST, ml.IS_MOIRA_GROUP, ml.IS_NFS_GROUP, mo.OWNER
HAVING 
    COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) > 1000;

all_runs.question: List the mailing lists with the largest number of members and the least number of members, including their names, owners, public status, hidden status, and number of members in the list. If a mailing list has multiple owners, create a separate entry for each owner. Similarly, if multiple lists share the minimum or maximum member count, include all those lists.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
WITH MemberCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS member_count
    FROM 
        MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld
    JOIN 
        MOIRA_LIST ml ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
    WHERE 
        ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
    GROUP BY 
        mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
),
MaxMinCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        MAX(member_count) AS max_count,
        MIN(member_count) AS min_count
    FROM 
        MemberCounts
),
TargetLists AS (
    SELECT 
        mc.MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        mc.member_count
    FROM 
        MemberCounts mc
    JOIN 
        MaxMinCounts mmc ON mc.member_count = mmc.max_count OR mc.member_count = mmc.min_count
)
SELECT 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    mlo.OWNER,
    ml.IS_PUBLIC,
    ml.IS_HIDDEN,
    tl.member_count
FROM 
    TargetLists tl
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST ml ON tl.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_OWNER mlo ON tl.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mlo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
ORDER BY 
    tl.member_count DESC, ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME, mlo.OWNER;

all_runs.question: For email lists with names starting with C (case insensitive) and containing faculty who teach courses in the summer in financial aid years after 2001, provide the name of the list, the number of people in the list, and the number of faculty in the list.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS total_members,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN ccso.SUMMER_INSTRUCTORS IS NOT NULL THEN mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER END) AS faculty_members
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    EMPLOYEE_DIRECTORY ed ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = ed.MIT_ID
JOIN 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED ccso ON ed.FULL_NAME = ccso.SUMMER_INSTRUCTORS
JOIN 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS at ON ccso.TERM_CODE = at.TERM_CODE
WHERE 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME LIKE 'C%' 
    AND at.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR > '2001'
    AND ccso.IS_OFFERED_SUMMER_TERM = 'Y'
GROUP BY 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME;

all_runs.question: Regarding the mailing list about duo users, provide the number of students in this list, and the number of departments and schools associated with these students.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    COUNT(DISTINCT msd.EMAIL_ADDRESS) AS number_of_students,
    COUNT(DISTINCT msd.DEPARTMENT) AS number_of_departments,
    COUNT(DISTINCT sd.SCHOOL_CODE) AS number_of_schools
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MIT_STUDENT_DIRECTORY msd ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER = msd.EMAIL_ADDRESS
JOIN 
    SIS_DEPARTMENT sd ON msd.DEPARTMENT = sd.DEPARTMENT_CODE
WHERE 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME = 'cat-duo-users';

all_runs.question: For faculty who are responsible for courses in 2023 fall term, list the name of mailing lists with ten members that they subscribe to, the number of faculty in these lists, and the number of courses associated with those faculty.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID) AS faculty_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT c.SUBJECT_ID) AS course_count
FROM 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED c
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON c.RESPONSIBLE_FACULTY_MIT_ID = mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST ml ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
WHERE 
    c.ACADEMIC_YEAR = '2023'
    AND c.IS_OFFERED_FALL_TERM = 'Y'
    AND ml.IS_ACTIVE = 'Y'
    AND ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
GROUP BY 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME
HAVING 
    COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID) = 10;

all_runs.question: For each course instructor in the 'keeper-zephyr' mailing list, provide the name of mailing lists they subscribe to, instructor name, earliest and latest publication years, and total number of enrolled students.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_FULL_NAME AS instructor_name,
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME AS mailing_list_name,
    MIN(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR) AS earliest_publication_year,
    MAX(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR) AS latest_publication_year,
    SUM(lso.NUM_ENROLLED_STUDENTS) AS total_enrolled_students
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR lci ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_FULL_NAME = lci.INSTRUCTOR_NAME
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrmd ON lci.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY = lrmd.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG lrc ON lrmd.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY = lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED lso ON lrmd.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = lso.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
WHERE 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME = 'keeper-zephyr'
GROUP BY 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_FULL_NAME, ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME;

all_runs.question: For each mailing list with a name beginning with R (case insensitive), and that Professor Ayden Hopkins is subscribed to, list its name, description, owner, number of people in the list, and number of tenured faculty in the list.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_DESCRIPTION,
    mo.OWNER,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS number_of_people,
    SUM(CASE WHEN sp.EMPLOYEE_TYPE = 'Faculty' AND sp.POSITION_TITLE LIKE '%Tenured%' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS number_of_tenured_faculty
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_OWNER mo ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY = mo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
LEFT JOIN 
    SE_PERSON sp ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = sp.MIT_ID
WHERE 
    ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
    AND ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME LIKE 'R%'
    AND EXISTS (
        SELECT 1
        FROM MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld_inner
        JOIN SE_PERSON sp_inner ON mld_inner.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = sp_inner.MIT_ID
        WHERE mld_inner.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
        AND sp_inner.FULL_NAME = 'Hopkins, Ayden'
        AND sp_inner.EMPLOYEE_TYPE = 'Faculty'
    )
GROUP BY 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME, ml.MOIRA_LIST_DESCRIPTION, mo.OWNER;

all_runs.question: For the email list with name 'date-destiny', list the name of the list, department name, the number of students from the Management department, and the percentage of students who are from the Management department, rounded to two decimal places.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    msd.DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    COUNT(msd.FULL_NAME) AS number_of_students,
    ROUND((COUNT(msd.FULL_NAME) / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM MIT_STUDENT_DIRECTORY WHERE DEPARTMENT_NAME = 'Management')) * 100, 2) AS percentage_of_students
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MIT_STUDENT_DIRECTORY msd ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_FULL_NAME = msd.FULL_NAME
WHERE 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME = 'date-destiny'
    AND msd.DEPARTMENT_NAME = 'Management'
GROUP BY 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME, msd.DEPARTMENT_NAME;

all_runs.question: For the building with the most floors, list the building name and the names of the mailing lists staring with a (case insensitive) that the building employees with kerberos starting with c (case insensitive) subscribe to.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT fb.BUILDING_NAME_LONG, mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME
FROM FAC_BUILDING fb
JOIN FAC_FLOOR ff ON fb.FAC_BUILDING_KEY = ff.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN EMPLOYEE_DIRECTORY ed ON ed.OFFICE_LOCATION LIKE CONCAT(fb.FAC_BUILDING_KEY, '%')
JOIN MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ed.KRB_NAME = mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER
JOIN MOIRA_LIST ml ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
WHERE fb.FAC_BUILDING_KEY = (
    SELECT ff.BUILDING_KEY
    FROM FAC_FLOOR ff
    GROUP BY ff.BUILDING_KEY
    ORDER BY COUNT(DISTINCT ff.FLOOR) DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
AND ed.KRB_NAME LIKE 'c%'
AND ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME LIKE 'a%';

all_runs.question: For the email lists subscribed by faculty members with last names begin with Y, list the names of the lists, the total number of subjects managed by faculty in those mailing lists, and the number of such faculty in the lists.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT ccs.SUBJECT_ID) AS total_subjects_managed,
    COUNT(DISTINCT ed.MIT_ID) AS number_of_faculty
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld
JOIN 
    EMPLOYEE_DIRECTORY ed ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = ed.MIT_ID
JOIN 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED ccs ON ccs.RESPONSIBLE_FACULTY_MIT_ID = ed.MIT_ID
WHERE 
    ed.LAST_NAME LIKE 'Y%'
GROUP BY 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME;

all_runs.question: For students with last names starting with H who are subscribed to mailing list 'beacon-date-date', list the names of the students, the phone numbers of departments they belong to, and the size of the mailing list 'beacon-date-date' that they are subscribed to.
all_runs.predicted_sql:

    msd.FULL_NAME AS student_name,
    sad.DEPARTMENT_PHONE_AREA_CODE,
    sad.DEPARTMENT_PHONE_NUMBER,

FROM

JOIN

    t.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR,
    t.ACADEMIC_YEAR,
    COUNT(DISTINCT tm.FISCAL_PERIOD) AS num_fiscal_periods,
    COUNT(DISTINCT tq.FY_QUARTER_CODE) AS num_quarters,
    MIN(at.TERM_START_DATE) AS start_term_date,
    MAX(at.TERM_END_DATE) AS end_term_date,
    COUNT(DISTINCT atp.TERM_PARAMETER) AS num_distinct_term_parameters
FROM 
    TIME_DAY t
LEFT JOIN 
    TIME_MONTH tm ON t.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR = tm.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR AND t.ACADEMIC_YEAR = tm.ACADEMIC_YEAR
LEFT JOIN 
    TIME_QUARTER tq ON t.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR = tq.FISCAL_YEAR
LEFT JOIN 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS at ON t.ACADEMIC_YEAR = at.ACADEMIC_YEAR
LEFT JOIN 
    ACADEMIC_TERM_PARAMETER atp ON at.TERM_CODE = atp.TERM_CODE
GROUP BY 
    t.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR, t.ACADEMIC_YEAR;

all_runs.question: Group buildings by campus sectors. For each group, list the campus sector, name of the building, city and state where the building is located, total number of floors, total assignable area, total number of rooms, total number of organizations, ownership type, and a rank column indicating the order (1-indexed) of this row within each sector based on the descending order of assignable area. Include subtotals for each sector and a grand total across all sectors. The subtotal and grand total only need to computed over the total number of floors and assignable area.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
WITH BuildingDetails AS (
    SELECT 
        fb.CAMPUS_SECTOR,
        fb.BUILDING_NAME_LONG,
        fba.CITY,
        fba.STATE,
        COUNT(DISTINCT ff.FCLT_FLOOR_KEY) AS TOTAL_FLOORS,
        SUM(ff.ASSIGNABLE_AREA) AS TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA,
        fb.NUM_OF_ROOMS,
        COUNT(DISTINCT fr.FCLT_ORGANIZATION_KEY) AS TOTAL_ORGANIZATIONS,
        fb.OWNERSHIP_TYPE
    FROM 
        FCLT_BUILDING fb
    LEFT JOIN 
        FCLT_BUILDING_ADDRESS fba ON fb.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY = fba.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY
    LEFT JOIN 
        FCLT_FLOOR ff ON fb.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY = ff.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY
    LEFT JOIN 
        FCLT_ROOMS fr ON fb.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY = fr.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY
    GROUP BY 
        fb.CAMPUS_SECTOR, fb.BUILDING_NAME_LONG, fba.CITY, fba.STATE, fb.NUM_OF_ROOMS, fb.OWNERSHIP_TYPE
),
RankedBuildings AS (
    SELECT 
        bd.*,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY bd.CAMPUS_SECTOR ORDER BY bd.TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA DESC) AS RANK_WITHIN_SECTOR
    FROM 
        BuildingDetails bd
),
SectorSubtotals AS (
    SELECT 
        CAMPUS_SECTOR,
        NULL AS BUILDING_NAME_LONG,
        NULL AS CITY,
        NULL AS STATE,
        SUM(TOTAL_FLOORS) AS TOTAL_FLOORS,
        SUM(TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA) AS TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA,
        NULL AS NUM_OF_ROOMS,
        NULL AS TOTAL_ORGANIZATIONS,
        NULL AS OWNERSHIP_TYPE,
        NULL AS RANK_WITHIN_SECTOR
    FROM 
        BuildingDetails
    GROUP BY 
        CAMPUS_SECTOR
),
GrandTotal AS (
    SELECT 
        'Grand Total' AS CAMPUS_SECTOR,
        NULL AS BUILDING_NAME_LONG,
        NULL AS CITY,
        NULL AS STATE,
        SUM(TOTAL_FLOORS) AS TOTAL_FLOORS,
        SUM(TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA) AS TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA,
        NULL AS NUM_OF_ROOMS,
        NULL AS TOTAL_ORGANIZATIONS,
        NULL AS OWNERSHIP_TYPE,
        NULL AS RANK_WITHIN_SECTOR
    FROM 
        BuildingDetails
)
SELECT * FROM RankedBuildings
UNION ALL
SELECT * FROM SectorSubtotals
UNION ALL
SELECT * FROM GrandTotal
ORDER BY 
    CAMPUS_SECTOR, RANK_WITHIN_SECTOR;

all_runs.question: For each department, list the name of the department, the title of the TIP material associated with the department, author, ISBN, library term code, and whether it is available in the library reserves ('Available in Library' if yes and 'Not Available in Library' otherwise), the total number of instructors per library book for the department, the total number of materials available in the library for the department, and the total number of available materials across all departments.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    tso.OFFER_DEPT_NAME AS Department_Name,
    tm.TITLE AS TIP_Material_Title,
    tm.AUTHOR AS TIP_Material_Author,
    tm.ISBN AS TIP_Material_ISBN,
    tso.TERM_CODE AS Library_Term_Code,
    CASE 
        WHEN lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY IS NOT NULL THEN 'Available in Library'
        ELSE 'Not Available in Library'
    END AS Library_Availability,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrm.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY) AS Total_Instructors_Per_Library_Book,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS Total_Materials_Available_In_Library,
    (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) FROM LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL) AS Total_Available_Materials_Across_All_Departments
FROM 
    TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED tso
LEFT JOIN 
    TIP_DETAIL td ON tso.TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = td.TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
LEFT JOIN 
    TIP_MATERIAL tm ON td.TIP_MATERIAL_KEY = tm.TIP_MATERIAL_KEY
LEFT JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrm ON td.SUBJECT_ID = lrm.SUBJECT_ID AND td.TERM_CODE = lrm.TERM_CODE
GROUP BY 
    tso.OFFER_DEPT_NAME, tm.TITLE, tm.AUTHOR, tm.ISBN, tso.TERM_CODE, Library_Availability
ORDER BY 
    tso.OFFER_DEPT_NAME;

all_runs.question: For each department and material status, list the name of the department, the material status, the number of TIP materials associated with this department and status, the number of library materials associated with this department and status, the total number of TIP and library materials associated with this department and status. Include a subtotal for each department and a grand total across all departments.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    COALESCE(tso.OFFER_DEPT_NAME, 'Total') AS Department,
    COALESCE(tms.TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS, lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS, 'Subtotal') AS Material_Status,
    COUNT(DISTINCT tm.TIP_MATERIAL_KEY) AS TIP_Material_Count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS Library_Material_Count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT tm.TIP_MATERIAL_KEY) + COUNT(DISTINCT lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS Total_Material_Count
FROM 
    TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED tso
LEFT JOIN 
    TIP_DETAIL td ON tso.TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = td.TIP_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
LEFT JOIN 
    TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS tms ON td.TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY = tms.TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY
LEFT JOIN 
    LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED lso ON tso.SUBJECT_ID = lso.SUBJECT_ID
LEFT JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrm ON lso.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = lrm.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
LEFT JOIN 
    LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS lms ON lrm.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY = lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY
GROUP BY 
    tso.OFFER_DEPT_NAME, tms.TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS, lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS
WITH ROLLUP
HAVING 
    (tso.OFFER_DEPT_NAME IS NOT NULL OR tms.TIP_MATERIAL_STATUS IS NOT NULL OR lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS IS NOT NULL)
ORDER BY 
    Department, Material_Status;

all_runs.question: For each building that is not a subdivision, list the building number, full name, street address, building type, occupancy date, ownership type, and site location. You should also include three rows at the end showing the number of owned, leased, all buildings at MIT that are not subdivisions, in the format of (null, #building Buildings, null, null, null, null, null).
all_runs.predicted_sql:

    f.BUILDING_NAME_LONG, 
    CONCAT(fa.STREET_NUMBER, ' ', fa.STREET_NAME, ' ', fa.STREET_SUFFIX) AS STREET_ADDRESS, 
    f.BUILDING_TYPE, 
    f.DATE_OCCUPIED, 
    f.OWNERSHIP_TYPE, 
    f.SITE
FROM 
    BUILDINGS b
JOIN 
    FAC_BUILDING f ON b.BUILDING_NUMBER = f.BUILDING_NUMBER
JOIN 
    FAC_BUILDING_ADDRESS fa ON b.BUILDING_KEY = fa.BUILDING_KEY
WHERE 
    f.PARENT_BUILDING_NUMBER IS NULL
    AND f.SITE = 'MIT'

UNION ALL

    CONCAT(COUNT(CASE WHEN f.OWNERSHIP_TYPE = 'OWNED' THEN 1 END), ' building Buildings'), 
    NULL, 
    NULL, 
    NULL, 
    NULL, 
    NULL
FROM 
    FAC_BUILDING f
WHERE 
    f.PARENT_BUILDING_NUMBER IS NULL
    AND f.SITE = 'MIT'

UNION ALL

SELECT 
    NULL, 
    CONCAT(COUNT(CASE WHEN f.OWNERSHIP_TYPE = 'LEASED' THEN 1 END), ' building Buildings'),

    NULL, 
    NULL, 
    NULL, 
    NULL
FROM 
    FAC_BUILDING f
WHERE 
    f.PARENT_BUILDING_NUMBER IS NULL
    AND f.SITE = 'MIT'

UNION ALL

SELECT 
    NULL, 
    CONCAT(COUNT(*), ' building Buildings'),

    NULL, 
    NULL, 
    NULL, 
    NULL
FROM 
    FAC_BUILDING f

    f.PARENT_BUILDING_NUMBER IS NULL
    AND f.SITE = 'MIT';

all_runs.question: For each owned building that is not a subdivision, list the construction start year, the building number, and the year of initial occupancy. Display the construction start year only if it differs from the previous row. If the year of initial occupancy or construction start year is unknown, display 'UNKNOWN'. You should also include a row at the end showing the total number of owned buildings that are not subdivisions, in the format of (null, #building Buildings, null).
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN @prev_date_built = DATE_BUILT THEN NULL 
        ELSE COALESCE(DATE_BUILT, 'UNKNOWN') 
    END AS construction_start_year,
    BUILDING_NUMBER,
    COALESCE(DATE_OCCUPIED, 'UNKNOWN') AS year_of_initial_occupancy
FROM (
    SELECT 
        DATE_FORMAT(STR_TO_DATE(DATE_BUILT, '%m/%d/%Y'), '%Y') AS DATE_BUILT,
        BUILDING_NUMBER,
        DATE_FORMAT(STR_TO_DATE(DATE_OCCUPIED, '%m/%d/%Y'), '%Y') AS DATE_OCCUPIED
    FROM FAC_BUILDING
    WHERE OWNERSHIP_TYPE = 'OWNED' AND PARENT_BUILDING_NUMBER IS NULL
    ORDER BY DATE_BUILT, BUILDING_NUMBER
) AS subquery
JOIN (SELECT @prev_date_built := NULL) AS init
ON 1=1
UNION ALL
SELECT 
    NULL,
    CONCAT(COUNT(*), ' Buildings'),
    NULL
FROM FAC_BUILDING
WHERE OWNERSHIP_TYPE = 'OWNED' AND PARENT_BUILDING_NUMBER IS NULL;

all_runs.question: Group all buildings at MIT into either owned or leased. For each group, state the ownership type, usage type, number of buildings, gross square footage, number of rooms, and the number of associated organizations. Display the ownership type only if it differs from the previous row. Include subtotals for each group and a grand total across all groups. The subtotal and grand total rows should not include ownership type and usage type. Footage should be rounded to integers and formatted using commas as thousands separators.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    IF(@prev_ownership = OWNERSHIP_TYPE, NULL, OWNERSHIP_TYPE) AS OWNERSHIP_TYPE,
    BUILDING_USE,
    COUNT(DISTINCT BUILDING_NUMBER) AS NUM_BUILDINGS,
    FORMAT(ROUND(SUM(EXT_GROSS_AREA)), 0) AS TOTAL_GROSS_SQ_FT,
    SUM(NUM_OF_ROOMS) AS TOTAL_NUM_ROOMS,
    COUNT(DISTINCT FCLT_ORGANIZATION_KEY) AS NUM_ORGANIZATIONS
FROM 
    FCLT_BUILDING_HIST b
LEFT JOIN 
    FCLT_ROOMS r ON b.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY = r.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY
WHERE 
    SITE = 'MIT'
GROUP BY 
    OWNERSHIP_TYPE, BUILDING_USE WITH ROLLUP
HAVING 
    (OWNERSHIP_TYPE IS NOT NULL AND BUILDING_USE IS NOT NULL) OR (OWNERSHIP_TYPE IS NULL AND BUILDING_USE IS NULL)
ORDER BY 
    OWNERSHIP_TYPE, BUILDING_USE;

all_runs.question: For each building use, list the type, the number of distinct buildings (excluding subdivisions) of this use, the total gross square footage of these buildings, and the number of unique organizations associated with the rooms in these buildings. If the building is used as a residence, display the usage type as "RESIDENTIAL." You should also include a row at the end showing the total number of buildings, the gross square footage, and the number of organizations across all types of building use. All numerical values should be rounded to integers and formatted using commas as thousands separators.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN b.BUILDING_USE = 'RESIDENT' THEN 'RESIDENTIAL'
        ELSE b.BUILDING_USE
    END AS BUILDING_USE,
    b.BUILDING_TYPE,
    FORMAT(COUNT(DISTINCT b.BUILDING_NUMBER), 0) AS DISTINCT_BUILDINGS,
    FORMAT(ROUND(SUM(b.EXT_GROSS_AREA)), 0) AS TOTAL_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,

all_runs.question: For each organization except Cambridge-MIT Institute, list its ID, number, level, formatted name according to level (if level is 2, there should be 1 space before the name, if level is 3, there should be 2 space before the name, up to level 6), whether it is assignable ('ASSIGNABLE' if assignable, 'NON-ASSIGNABLE' otherwise), total area, number of rooms, and average room area. all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    o.ORGANIZATION_ID,
    o.ORGANIZATION_NUMBER,
    o.ORGANIZATION_LEVEL,
    CONCAT(REPEAT(' ', o.ORGANIZATION_LEVEL - 1), o.ORGANIZATION_NAME) AS FORMATTED_NAME,
    CASE o.ASSIGNABLE WHEN '1' THEN 'ASSIGNABLE' ELSE 'NON-ASSIGNABLE' END AS ASSIGNABLE_STATUS,

all_runs.question: Group all rooms into whether or not they are assignable and the major use descriptions. For each group, state "ASSIGNABLE" if the room is assignable and "NON-ASSIGNABLE" otherwise, the major use description, the total number of rooms, total area, and average area. Include subtotals for each group and a grand total across all groups. The assignable status and major use descriptions should only be displayed when they differ from the previous row. Do not include rooms whose major use or major use description starts with 'ZUSE.' The results should be sorted by assignable status and major use description. The subtotal and grand total rows should not include assignable status or major use description.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN fm.ASSIGNABLE = '1' THEN 'ASSIGNABLE' 
        ELSE 'NON-ASSIGNABLE' 
    END AS ASSIGNABLE_STATUS,
    fr.MAJOR_USE_DESC,
    COUNT(*) AS TOTAL_ROOMS,
    SUM(fr.AREA) AS TOTAL_AREA,
    AVG(fr.AREA) AS AVERAGE_AREA
FROM 
    FCLT_ROOMS fr

all_runs.question: List each floor key and department name within the Stata building, as well as the number of rooms, total area, and average area per department on each floor. Include subtotals for each floor and a grand total across all floors. Sort the results by floor key and department name in ascending order. Exclude departments without any rooms in the building. Only the first row of each floor group should include the floor key, and the subtotal and grand total rows should not include floor key or department name. Number of rooms and area should be rounded to integers and formatted using commas as thousands separators.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
WITH RoomDetails AS (
    SELECT 
        fr.FLOOR_KEY,
        fo.ORGANIZATION_NAME,
        COUNT(*) AS room_count,
        SUM(CAST(fr.AREA AS DECIMAL(10, 2))) AS total_area
    FROM 
        FAC_ROOMS fr
    JOIN 
        BUILDINGS b ON fr.BUILDING_KEY = b.BUILDING_KEY
    JOIN 
        FCLT_ORGANIZATION fo ON fr.ORGANIZATION_KEY = fo.FCLT_ORGANIZATION_KEY
    WHERE 
        b.BUILDING_NAME = 'Stata'
    GROUP BY 
        fr.FLOOR_KEY, fo.ORGANIZATION_NAME
),
FloorSubtotals AS (
    SELECT 
        FLOOR_KEY,
        NULL AS ORGANIZATION_NAME,
        SUM(room_count) AS room_count,
        SUM(total_area) AS total_area
    FROM 
        RoomDetails
    GROUP BY 
        FLOOR_KEY
),
GrandTotal AS (
    SELECT 
        NULL AS FLOOR_KEY,
        NULL AS ORGANIZATION_NAME,
        SUM(room_count) AS room_count,
        SUM(total_area) AS total_area
    FROM 
        RoomDetails
)
SELECT 
    FLOOR_KEY,
    ORGANIZATION_NAME,
    FORMAT(room_count, 0) AS room_count,
    FORMAT(total_area, 0) AS total_area,
    FORMAT(ROUND(total_area / room_count, 0), 0) AS avg_area
FROM 
    RoomDetails
UNION ALL
SELECT 
    FLOOR_KEY,
    ORGANIZATION_NAME,
    FORMAT(room_count, 0) AS room_count,
    FORMAT(total_area, 0) AS total_area,
    NULL AS avg_area
FROM 
    FloorSubtotals
UNION ALL
SELECT 
    FLOOR_KEY,
    ORGANIZATION_NAME,
    FORMAT(room_count, 0) AS room_count,
    FORMAT(total_area, 0) AS total_area,
    NULL AS avg_area
FROM 
    GrandTotal
ORDER BY 
    FLOOR_KEY IS NULL, FLOOR_KEY, ORGANIZATION_NAME IS NULL, ORGANIZATION_NAME;

all_runs.question: List each building key and floor key within the department of facilities, the number of rooms, total area, average area per floor, building name, access level, zip code, and city. Include subtotals for each building and a grand total across all buildings. The subtotals and grand total should not include zip code or city. Numbers of rooms and area should be rounded to integers and formatted using commas as thousands separators.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    b.BUILDING_KEY,
    f.FLOOR_KEY,
    COUNT(r.FAC_ROOM_KEY) AS 'Number of Rooms',
    FORMAT(SUM(CAST(r.AREA AS DECIMAL(10,2))), 0) AS 'Total Area',
    FORMAT(AVG(CAST(r.AREA AS DECIMAL(10,2))), 0) AS 'Average Area per Floor',
    b.BUILDING_NAME_LONG AS 'Building Name',
    b.ACCESS_LEVEL_CODE AS 'Access Level',
    a.POSTAL_CODE AS 'Zip Code',
    a.CITY AS 'City'
FROM 
    FAC_BUILDING b
JOIN 
    FAC_ROOMS r ON b.FAC_BUILDING_KEY = r.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_FLOOR f ON b.FAC_BUILDING_KEY = f.BUILDING_KEY AND r.FLOOR_KEY = f.FLOOR_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_BUILDING_ADDRESS a ON b.FAC_BUILDING_KEY = a.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_ORGANIZATION o ON r.ORGANIZATION_KEY = o.ORGANIZATION_KEY
WHERE 
    o.ORGANIZATION_NAME = 'Department of Facilities'
GROUP BY 
    b.BUILDING_KEY, f.FLOOR_KEY, b.BUILDING_NAME_LONG, b.ACCESS_LEVEL_CODE, a.POSTAL_CODE, a.CITY
WITH ROLLUP
HAVING 
    GROUPING(b.BUILDING_KEY) = 0 OR GROUPING(f.FLOOR_KEY) = 1
ORDER BY 
    b.BUILDING_KEY, f.FLOOR_KEY;

all_runs.question: List the department, school, course number, subject title, total number of enrolled students, term code, and count of distinct catalog ISBNs. Add a summary row at the bottom showing the total number of students and distinct catalog ISBNs for the current term in the format of ('TOTAL:', null, null, null, total number of students, null, number of distinct catalog ISBNs).
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT

    lso.OFFER_SCHOOL_NAME AS school,
    lso.COURSE_NUMBER AS course_number,

JOIN

all_runs.question: For each mailing list that involves subscribers that work in departments with names starting with 'Computer Science', state the ownership type, the list name, the number of owners, and the number of subscribers. Display the ownership type only if it differs from the previous entry. Include subtotals (the corresponding type field shoud be 'SUBTOTAL') for each ownership type and a grand total (the corresponding type field shoud be 'TOTAL') across all ownership types.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
WITH ListDetails AS (
    SELECT 
        mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID,
        mlo.OWNER_TYPE
    FROM 
        MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld
    JOIN 
        EMPLOYEE_DIRECTORY ed ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = ed.MIT_ID
    JOIN 
        MOIRA_LIST_OWNER mlo ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY = mlo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
    WHERE 
        ed.DEPARTMENT_NAME LIKE 'Computer Science%'
),
OwnerCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        OWNER_TYPE,
        COUNT(DISTINCT OWNER_TYPE) AS OwnerCount
    FROM 
        ListDetails
    GROUP BY 
        MOIRA_LIST_KEY, OWNER_TYPE
),
SubscriberCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        COUNT(DISTINCT MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID) AS SubscriberCount
    FROM 
        ListDetails
    GROUP BY 
        MOIRA_LIST_KEY
),
FinalCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        ld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        ld.OWNER_TYPE,
        oc.OwnerCount,
        sc.SubscriberCount
    FROM 
        ListDetails ld
    JOIN 
        OwnerCounts oc ON ld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = oc.MOIRA_LIST_KEY AND ld.OWNER_TYPE = oc.OWNER_TYPE
    JOIN 
        SubscriberCounts sc ON ld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = sc.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
),
DistinctOwnerTypes AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT OWNER_TYPE FROM FinalCounts
),
Subtotals AS (
    SELECT 
        'SUBTOTAL' AS OWNER_TYPE,

all_runs.question: For each term code, list the term description, attribute desciption, department name, school name, and the number of subjects in the area of humanities, arts and social sciences.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    a.TERM_CODE,
    a.TERM_DESCRIPTION,
    c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE_DESC,
    d.DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    d.SCHOOL_NAME,
    COUNT(*) AS NUM_SUBJECTS
FROM 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS_ALL a
JOIN 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED b ON a.TERM_CODE = b.TERM_CODE
JOIN 
    CIS_HASS_ATTRIBUTE c ON FIND_IN_SET(c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE, b.HASS_ATTRIBUTE) > 0
JOIN 
    SIS_DEPARTMENT d ON b.DEPARTMENT_CODE = d.DEPARTMENT_CODE
WHERE 
    c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE_DESC IN ('HASS Humanities', 'HASS Arts', 'HASS Social Sciences')
GROUP BY 
    a.TERM_CODE, a.TERM_DESCRIPTION, c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE_DESC, d.DEPARTMENT_NAME, d.SCHOOL_NAME;

all_runs.question: List building names, their height, street address, city, state, postal code, their gross and assignable square footage, the smallest and largest floor level and the total area of all rooms for each building key.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    b.BUILDING_NAME,
    fb.BUILDING_HEIGHT,
    CONCAT(fba.STREET_NUMBER, ' ', fba.STREET_NAME, ' ', fba.STREET_SUFFIX) AS STREET_ADDRESS,
    fba.CITY,
    fba.STATE,
    fba.POSTAL_CODE,
    b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    MIN(ff.FLOOR) AS SMALLEST_FLOOR_LEVEL,
    MAX(ff.FLOOR) AS LARGEST_FLOOR_LEVEL,
    SUM(fr.AREA) AS TOTAL_ROOM_AREA
FROM 
    BUILDINGS b
JOIN 
    FAC_BUILDING_ADDRESS fba ON b.BUILDING_KEY = fba.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_FLOOR ff ON b.BUILDING_KEY = ff.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_ROOMS fr ON b.BUILDING_KEY = fr.BUILDING_KEY
GROUP BY 
    b.BUILDING_KEY, b.BUILDING_NAME, fb.BUILDING_HEIGHT, fba.STREET_NUMBER, fba.STREET_NAME, fba.STREET_SUFFIX, fba.CITY, fba.STATE, fba.POSTAL_CODE, b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE, b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE;

all_runs.question: What is the category title, version, department name, school name, total number of courses for each course level, and the total number of degree-granting courses for each CIP category code?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    c.CATEGORY_TITLE,
    c.VERSION,
    s.DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    s.SCHOOL_NAME,
    sc.COURSE_LEVEL,
    COUNT(sc.COURSE) AS total_courses,
    SUM(CASE WHEN sc.IS_DEGREE_GRANTING = 'Y' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS total_degree_granting_courses
FROM 
    CIP c
JOIN 
    SIS_COURSE_DESCRIPTION sc ON c.PROGRAM_CODE = sc.CIP_PROGRAM_CODE
JOIN 
    SIS_DEPARTMENT s ON sc.DEPARTMENT = s.DEPARTMENT_CODE
GROUP BY 
    c.CATEGORY_TITLE, c.VERSION, s.DEPARTMENT_NAME, s.SCHOOL_NAME, sc.COURSE_LEVEL
ORDER BY 
    c.CATEGORY_TITLE, c.VERSION, s.DEPARTMENT_NAME, s.SCHOOL_NAME, sc.COURSE_LEVEL;

all_runs.question: What is the total number of library materials, the minimum and maximum publication years, and the total number of materials status for each course name?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    lci.COURSE_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS total_library_materials,
    MIN(CAST(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR AS UNSIGNED)) AS min_publication_year,
    MAX(CAST(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR AS UNSIGNED)) AS max_publication_year,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrm.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY) AS total_material_status
FROM 
    LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR lci
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrmd ON lci.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY = lrmd.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG lrc ON lrmd.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY = lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS lrm ON lrmd.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY = lrm.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY
GROUP BY 
    lci.COURSE_NAME;

all_runs.question: What is the total number of library reserve materials, the minimum and maximum publication years, and the total number of enrolled students for each course instructor?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    lci.INSTRUCTOR_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS total_library_reserve_materials,
    MIN(CAST(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR AS UNSIGNED)) AS min_publication_year,
    MAX(CAST(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR AS UNSIGNED)) AS max_publication_year,
    SUM(lso.NUM_ENROLLED_STUDENTS) AS total_enrolled_students
FROM 
    LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR lci
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrm ON lci.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY = lrm.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG lrc ON lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY = lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED lso ON lrm.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = lso.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
GROUP BY 
    lci.INSTRUCTOR_NAME;

all_runs.question: What is the material status, term description, total number of courses and materials, occurences in departments and school, and the total number of instructors for each library material status code and term code?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_CODE,
    ata.TERM_DESCRIPTION,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lcid.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY) AS total_courses,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY) AS total_materials,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lso.OFFER_DEPT_CODE) AS occurrences_in_departments,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lso.OFFER_SCHOOL_NAME) AS occurrences_in_schools,
    COUNT(DISTINCT lci.INSTRUCTOR_NAME) AS total_instructors
FROM 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrm
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS lms ON lrm.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY = lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_KEY
JOIN 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS_ALL ata ON lrm.TERM_CODE = ata.TERM_CODE
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR lci ON lrm.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY = lci.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG lrc ON lrm.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY = lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED lso ON lrm.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = lso.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
GROUP BY 
    lms.LIBRARY_MATERIAL_STATUS_CODE, ata.TERM_DESCRIPTION;

all_runs.question: For each distinct mailing list containing more than 1000 people and with a name starting with A (case insensitive), provide its name, whether it is a mailing list, whether it is a moira group, whether it is a NFS group, the owner of the mailing list, and the number of people in the list.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST,
    ml.IS_MOIRA_GROUP,
    ml.IS_NFS_GROUP,
    mo.OWNER,
    COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS number_of_people
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_OWNER mo ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY = mo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
WHERE 
    ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
    AND ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME LIKE 'A%'
GROUP BY 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME, ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST, ml.IS_MOIRA_GROUP, ml.IS_NFS_GROUP, mo.OWNER
HAVING 
    COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) > 1000;

all_runs.question: List the mailing lists with the largest number of members and the least number of members, including their names, owners, public status, hidden status, and number of members in the list. If a mailing list has multiple owners, create a separate entry for each owner. Similarly, if multiple lists share the minimum or maximum member count, include all those lists.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
WITH MemberCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS member_count
    FROM 
        MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld
    JOIN 
        MOIRA_LIST ml ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
    WHERE 
        ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
    GROUP BY 
        mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
),
MaxMinCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        MAX(member_count) AS max_count,
        MIN(member_count) AS min_count
    FROM 
        MemberCounts
),
TargetLists AS (
    SELECT 
        mc.MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        mc.member_count
    FROM 
        MemberCounts mc
    JOIN 
        MaxMinCounts mmc ON mc.member_count = mmc.max_count OR mc.member_count = mmc.min_count
)
SELECT 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    mlo.OWNER,
    ml.IS_PUBLIC,
    ml.IS_HIDDEN,
    tl.member_count
FROM 
    TargetLists tl
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST ml ON tl.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON tl.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_OWNER mlo ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY = mlo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
WHERE 
    ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
ORDER BY 
    tl.member_count DESC, ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME, mlo.OWNER;

all_runs.question: For email lists with names starting with C (case insensitive) and containing faculty who teach courses in the summer in financial aid years after 2001, provide the name of the list, the number of people in the list, and the number of faculty in the list.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS total_members,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN ccso.SUMMER_INSTRUCTORS IS NOT NULL THEN mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER END) AS faculty_count
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    EMPLOYEE_DIRECTORY ed ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = ed.MIT_ID
JOIN 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED ccso ON ed.FULL_NAME = ccso.SUMMER_INSTRUCTORS
JOIN 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS at ON ccso.TERM_CODE = at.TERM_CODE
WHERE 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME LIKE 'C%' 
    AND at.FINANCIAL_AID_YEAR > '2001'
    AND ccso.IS_OFFERED_SUMMER_TERM = 'Y'
GROUP BY 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME;

all_runs.question: Regarding the mailing list about duo users, provide the number of students in this list, and the number of departments and schools associated with these students.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    COUNT(DISTINCT msd.EMAIL_ADDRESS) AS number_of_students,
    COUNT(DISTINCT msd.DEPARTMENT) AS number_of_departments,
    COUNT(DISTINCT sd.SCHOOL_CODE) AS number_of_schools
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MIT_STUDENT_DIRECTORY msd ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER = msd.EMAIL_ADDRESS
JOIN 
    SIS_DEPARTMENT sd ON msd.DEPARTMENT = sd.DEPARTMENT_CODE
WHERE 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME = 'cat-duo-users';

all_runs.question: For faculty who are responsible for courses in 2023 fall term, list the name of mailing lists with ten members that they subscribe to, the number of faculty in these lists, and the number of courses associated with those faculty.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID) AS faculty_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT ccs.SUBJECT_ID) AS course_count
FROM 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED ccs
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ccs.RESPONSIBLE_FACULTY_MIT_ID = mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST ml ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
WHERE 
    ccs.ACADEMIC_YEAR = '2023'
    AND ccs.IS_OFFERED_FALL_TERM = 'Y'
    AND ml.IS_ACTIVE = 'Y'
    AND ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
GROUP BY 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME
HAVING 
    COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID) = 10;

all_runs.question: For each course instructor in the 'keeper-zephyr' mailing list, provide the name of mailing lists they subscribe to, instructor name, earliest and latest publication years, and total number of enrolled students.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_FULL_NAME AS instructor_name,
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME AS mailing_list_name,
    MIN(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR) AS earliest_publication_year,
    MAX(lrc.CATALOG_YEAR) AS latest_publication_year,
    SUM(lso.NUM_ENROLLED_STUDENTS) AS total_enrolled_students
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR lci ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_FULL_NAME = lci.INSTRUCTOR_NAME
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_MATRL_DETAIL lrmd ON lci.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY = lrmd.LIBRARY_COURSE_INSTRUCTOR_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG lrc ON lrmd.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY = lrc.LIBRARY_RESERVE_CATALOG_KEY
JOIN 
    LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED lso ON lrmd.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY = lso.LIBRARY_SUBJECT_OFFERED_KEY
WHERE 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME = 'keeper-zephyr'
GROUP BY 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_FULL_NAME, ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME;

all_runs.question: For each mailing list with a name beginning with R (case insensitive), and that Professor Ayden Hopkins is subscribed to, list its name, description, owner, number of people in the list, and number of tenured faculty in the list.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_DESCRIPTION,
    mo.OWNER,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS number_of_people,
    SUM(CASE WHEN sp.EMPLOYEE_TYPE = 'Faculty' AND sp.POSITION_TITLE LIKE '%Tenured%' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS number_of_tenured_faculty
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_OWNER mo ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY = mo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
JOIN 
    SE_PERSON sp ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = sp.MIT_ID
WHERE 
    ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
    AND ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME LIKE 'R%'
    AND EXISTS (
        SELECT 1
        FROM MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld2
        JOIN SE_PERSON sp2 ON mld2.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER_MIT_ID = sp2.MIT_ID
        WHERE mld2.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
        AND sp2.FULL_NAME = 'Hopkins, Ayden'
    )
GROUP BY

all_runs.question: For the building with the most floors, list the building name and the names of the mailing lists staring with a (case insensitive) that the building employees with kerberos starting with c (case insensitive) subscribe to.

all_runs.question: Group biology courses by cluster type and course level.     AVG(sos.CLUSTER_ENROLLMENT_NUMBER) AS average_cluster_enrollment,
    scd.COURSE_LEVEL AS course_level,

all_runs.question: For subjects offered this year in either the Fall or Spring term, list its department name, school name, subject ID, subject title, course level, total units, the term it is offered ('Spring' for Spring term and 'Fall' for Fall term), term description, the number of distinct instructors teaching in the Fall, and the number of distinct instructors teaching in the Spring.

    COUNT(r.FAC_ROOM_KEY) AS 'Number of Rooms',
    FORMAT(SUM(CAST(r.AREA AS DECIMAL(10,2))), 0) AS 'Total Area',
    FORMAT(AVG(CAST(f.EXT_GROSS_AREA AS DECIMAL(10,2))), 0) AS 'Average Area per Floor',
    b.BUILDING_NAME_LONG AS 'Building Name',
    b.ACCESS_LEVEL_CODE AS 'Access Level',
    a.POSTAL_CODE AS 'Zip Code',
    a.CITY AS 'City'
FROM 
    FAC_BUILDING b
JOIN 
    FAC_ROOMS r ON b.FAC_BUILDING_KEY = r.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_FLOOR f ON b.FAC_BUILDING_KEY = f.BUILDING_KEY AND r.FLOOR_KEY = f.FLOOR_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_BUILDING_ADDRESS a ON b.FAC_BUILDING_KEY = a.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_ORGANIZATION o ON r.ORGANIZATION_KEY = o.ORGANIZATION_KEY
WHERE 
    o.ORGANIZATION_NAME = 'Department of Facilities'
GROUP BY 
    b.BUILDING_KEY, f.FLOOR_KEY, b.BUILDING_NAME_LONG, b.ACCESS_LEVEL_CODE, a.POSTAL_CODE, a.CITY
WITH ROLLUP
HAVING 
    (GROUPING(b.BUILDING_KEY) = 0 AND GROUPING(f.FLOOR_KEY) = 0) OR
    (GROUPING(b.BUILDING_KEY) = 0 AND GROUPING(f.FLOOR_KEY) = 1) OR
    (GROUPING(b.BUILDING_KEY) = 1 AND GROUPING(f.FLOOR_KEY) = 1)
ORDER BY 
    b.BUILDING_KEY, f.FLOOR_KEY;

all_runs.question: For each mailing list that involves subscribers that work in departments with names starting with 'Computer Science', state the ownership type, the list name, the number of owners, and the number of subscribers.     FROM

    JOIN

    WHERE

    GROUP BY 
        mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
),
ListOwners AS (
    SELECT 
        mlo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY,
        COUNT(DISTINCT mlo.OWNER) AS owner_count

    GROUP BY 
        mlo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
),
ListDetails AS (
    SELECT 
        ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
        mlo.OWNER_TYPE,
        ls.subscriber_count,

all_runs.question: What are the academic year, and instructors names for courses offered in the academic year 2022, along with the total number of types of courses per instructor?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    a.ACADEMIC_YEAR,
    e.FULL_NAME AS INSTRUCTOR_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT s.MASTER_COURSE_NUMBER) AS TOTAL_COURSE_TYPES
FROM 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS_ALL a
JOIN 
    SUBJECT_OFFERED s ON a.TERM_CODE = s.TERM_CODE
JOIN 
    EMPLOYEE_DIRECTORY e ON s.RESPONSIBLE_FACULTY_MIT_ID = e.MIT_ID
WHERE 
    a.ACADEMIC_YEAR = '2022'
GROUP BY 
    a.ACADEMIC_YEAR, e.FULL_NAME;

all_runs.question: What are the building names, department names, organizations, their highest and lowest floor number, along with the total number of rooms per each building key?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    fb.BUILDING_NAME_LONG AS building_name,
    fr.ORGANIZATION_NAME AS department_name,
    fo.ORGANIZATION AS organization,
    MIN(ff.FLOOR) AS lowest_floor_number,
    MAX(ff.FLOOR) AS highest_floor_number,
    COUNT(DISTINCT fr.FAC_ROOM_KEY) AS total_number_of_rooms
FROM 
    FAC_BUILDING fb
JOIN 
    FAC_ROOMS fr ON fb.FAC_BUILDING_KEY = fr.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_FLOOR ff ON fr.FLOOR_KEY = ff.FLOOR_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_ORGANIZATION fo ON fr.ORGANIZATION_KEY = fo.ORGANIZATION_KEY
GROUP BY 
    fb.BUILDING_NAME_LONG, fr.ORGANIZATION_NAME, fo.ORGANIZATION;

all_runs.question: Provide the complete information for students with the first name Kevin, including their full names, email addresses, department names, department phone numbers, school names, and the total student count per department and school. If a student is associated with more than one department, list a separate row for each department.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    msd.FULL_NAME,
    msd.EMAIL_ADDRESS,
    msd.DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    CONCAT(sad.DEPARTMENT_PHONE_AREA_CODE, sad.DEPARTMENT_PHONE_NUMBER) AS DEPARTMENT_PHONE_NUMBER,
    sd.SCHOOL_NAME,
    COUNT(msd.FULL_NAME) OVER (PARTITION BY msd.DEPARTMENT_NAME) AS STUDENT_COUNT_PER_DEPARTMENT,
    COUNT(msd.FULL_NAME) OVER (PARTITION BY sd.SCHOOL_NAME) AS STUDENT_COUNT_PER_SCHOOL
FROM 
    MIT_STUDENT_DIRECTORY msd
LEFT JOIN 
    SIS_ADMIN_DEPARTMENT sad ON msd.DEPARTMENT = sad.SIS_ADMIN_DEPARTMENT_CODE
LEFT JOIN 
    SIS_DEPARTMENT sd ON msd.DEPARTMENT = sd.DEPARTMENT_CODE
WHERE 
    msd.FIRST_NAME = 'Kevin';

all_runs.question: What are the unique titles of subjects offered in the fall term along with their instructor names, instructor emails, and the total number of types of subjects per instructor?

all_runs.question: List the building names, names of HR departments occupying them, the total gross square footage, the total and average assignable square footage, and the built year per building key.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    b.BUILDING_NAME,
    fo.HR_DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    SUM(b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE) AS TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    AVG(b.BLDG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE) AS AVG_ASSIGNABLE_SQUARE_FOOTAGE,
    fb.DATE_BUILT
FROM 
    BUILDINGS b
JOIN 
    FAC_ROOMS fr ON b.BUILDING_KEY = fr.BUILDING_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_ORGANIZATION fo ON fr.ORGANIZATION_KEY = fo.ORGANIZATION_KEY

    FAC_BUILDING fb ON b.BUILDING_NUMBER = fb.BUILDING_NUMBER
GROUP BY 
    b.BUILDING_KEY, b.BUILDING_NAME, fo.HR_DEPARTMENT_NAME, b.BLDG_GROSS_SQUARE_FOOTAGE, fb.DATE_BUILT;

all_runs.question: Retrieve the titles of subjects offered in the summer term along with their descriptions, responsible faculty names, email address, building name, room name, floor level, building street address, and the total number of types of courses per departmnet.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    c.SUBJECT_TITLE,
    c.SUBJECT_DESCRIPTION,
    c.RESPONSIBLE_FACULTY_NAME,
    e.EMAIL_ADDRESS,
    b.BUILDING_NAME,
    r.ROOM_FULL_NAME,
    f.FLOOR,
    b.BUILDING_STREET_ADDRESS,
    COUNT(DISTINCT c.SUBJECT_CODE) AS TOTAL_COURSE_TYPES_PER_DEPARTMENT
FROM 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED c
JOIN 
    EMPLOYEE_DIRECTORY e ON c.RESPONSIBLE_FACULTY_MIT_ID = e.MIT_ID
JOIN 
    FAC_ROOMS r ON c.MEET_PLACE = r.FAC_ROOM_KEY
JOIN 
    FAC_FLOOR f ON r.FLOOR_KEY = f.FLOOR_KEY
JOIN 
    BUILDINGS b ON r.BUILDING_KEY = b.BUILDING_KEY
WHERE 
    c.IS_OFFERED_SUMMER_TERM = 'Y'
GROUP BY 
    c.SUBJECT_TITLE, 
    c.SUBJECT_DESCRIPTION, 
    c.RESPONSIBLE_FACULTY_NAME, 
    e.EMAIL_ADDRESS, 
    b.BUILDING_NAME, 
    r.ROOM_FULL_NAME, 
    f.FLOOR, 
    b.BUILDING_STREET_ADDRESS;

all_runs.question: For each term code, list the term description, attribute desciption, department name, school name, and the number of subjects in the area of humanities, arts and social sciences.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    a.TERM_CODE,
    a.TERM_DESCRIPTION,
    c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE_DESC,
    d.DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    d.SCHOOL_NAME,
    COUNT(*) AS NUM_SUBJECTS
FROM 
    ACADEMIC_TERMS_ALL a
JOIN 
    COURSE_CATALOG_SUBJECT_OFFERED b ON a.TERM_CODE = b.TERM_CODE
JOIN 
    CIS_HASS_ATTRIBUTE c ON FIND_IN_SET(c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE, b.HASS_ATTRIBUTE) > 0
JOIN 
    SIS_DEPARTMENT d ON b.DEPARTMENT_CODE = d.DEPARTMENT_CODE
WHERE 
    c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE_DESC IN ('HASS Humanities', 'HASS Arts', 'HASS Social Sciences')
GROUP BY 
    a.TERM_CODE, a.TERM_DESCRIPTION, c.HASS_ATTRIBUTE_DESC, d.DEPARTMENT_NAME, d.SCHOOL_NAME;

all_runs.question: List building names, their height, street address, city, state, postal code, their gross and assignable square footage, the smallest and largest floor level and the total area of all rooms for each building key.
all_runs.predicted_sql:

    fb.BUILDING_HEIGHT,
    fba.STREET_NUMBER || ' ' || fba.STREET_NAME || ' ' || fba.STREET_SUFFIX AS STREET_ADDRESS,
    fba.CITY,

all_runs.question: What is the category title, version, department name, school name, total number of courses for each course level, and the total number of degree-granting courses for each CIP category code?
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    c.CATEGORY_TITLE,
    c.VERSION,
    s.DEPARTMENT_NAME,
    s.SCHOOL_NAME,
    sc.COURSE_LEVEL,
    COUNT(sc.COURSE) AS total_courses,
    SUM(CASE WHEN sc.IS_DEGREE_GRANTING = 'Y' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS total_degree_granting_courses

all_runs.question: For each distinct mailing list containing more than 1000 people and with a name starting with A (case insensitive), provide its name, whether it is a mailing list, whether it is a moira group, whether it is a NFS group, the owner of the mailing list, and the number of people in the list.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST,
    ml.IS_MOIRA_GROUP,
    ml.IS_NFS_GROUP,
    mo.OWNER,
    COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS number_of_people
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld ON ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_OWNER mo ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY = mo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
WHERE 
    ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
    AND ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME LIKE 'A%'
GROUP BY 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME, ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST, ml.IS_MOIRA_GROUP, ml.IS_NFS_GROUP, mo.OWNER
HAVING 
    COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) > 1000;

all_runs.question: List the mailing lists with the largest number of members and the least number of members, including their names, owners, public status, hidden status, and number of members in the list. If a mailing list has multiple owners, create a separate entry for each owner. Similarly, if multiple lists share the minimum or maximum member count, include all those lists.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
WITH MemberCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        COUNT(mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS member_count
    FROM 
        MOIRA_LIST_DETAIL mld
    JOIN 
        MOIRA_LIST ml ON mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
    WHERE 
        ml.IS_MOIRA_MAILING_LIST = 'Y'
    GROUP BY 
        mld.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
),
MaxMinCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        MAX(member_count) AS max_count,
        MIN(member_count) AS min_count
    FROM 
        MemberCounts
),
TargetLists AS (
    SELECT 
        mc.MOIRA_LIST_KEY,
        mc.member_count
    FROM 
        MemberCounts mc
    JOIN 
        MaxMinCounts mmc ON mc.member_count = mmc.max_count OR mc.member_count = mmc.min_count
)
SELECT 
    ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    mlo.OWNER,
    ml.IS_PUBLIC,
    ml.IS_HIDDEN,
    tl.member_count
FROM 
    TargetLists tl
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST ml ON tl.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = ml.MOIRA_LIST_KEY
JOIN 
    MOIRA_LIST_OWNER mlo ON tl.MOIRA_LIST_KEY = mlo.MOIRA_LIST_OWNER_KEY
ORDER BY 
    tl.member_count DESC, ml.MOIRA_LIST_NAME, mlo.OWNER;

all_runs.question: For email lists with names starting with C (case insensitive) and containing faculty who teach courses in the summer in financial aid years after 2001, provide the name of the list, the number of people in the list, and the number of faculty in the list.
all_runs.predicted_sql:
SELECT 
    mld.MOIRA_LIST_NAME,
    COUNT(DISTINCT mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER) AS total_members,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN ccso.SUMMER_INSTRUCTORS IS NOT NULL THEN mld.MOIRA_LIST_MEMBER END) AS faculty_count
FROM 
    MOIRA_LIST ml
JOIN

all_runs.question: Group buildings by campus sectors.         fb.CAMPUS_SECTOR,
        fb.BUILDING_NAME_LONG,
        fba.CITY,
        fba.STATE,
        COUNT(DISTINCT ff.FCLT_FLOOR_KEY) AS TOTAL_FLOORS,
        SUM(ff.ASSIGNABLE_AREA) AS TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA,
        fb.NUM_OF_ROOMS,
        COUNT(DISTINCT fr.FCLT_ORGANIZATION_KEY) AS TOTAL_ORGANIZATIONS,
        fb.OWNERSHIP_TYPE
    FROM 
        FCLT_BUILDING fb
    LEFT JOIN 
        FCLT_BUILDING_ADDRESS fba ON fb.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY = fba.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY
    LEFT JOIN 
        FCLT_FLOOR ff ON fb.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY = ff.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY
    LEFT JOIN 
        FCLT_ROOMS fr ON fb.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY = fr.FCLT_BUILDING_KEY
    GROUP BY 
        fb.CAMPUS_SECTOR, fb.BUILDING_NAME_LONG, fba.CITY, fba.STATE, fb.NUM_OF_ROOMS, fb.OWNERSHIP_TYPE
),
RankedBuildings AS (
    SELECT 
        bd.*,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY bd.CAMPUS_SECTOR ORDER BY bd.TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA DESC) AS RANK_WITHIN_SECTOR
    FROM 
        BuildingDetails bd
),
SectorSubtotals AS (
    SELECT 
        CAMPUS_SECTOR,
        NULL AS BUILDING_NAME_LONG,
        NULL AS CITY,
        NULL AS STATE,
        SUM(TOTAL_FLOORS) AS TOTAL_FLOORS,

        NULL AS NUM_OF_ROOMS,
        NULL AS TOTAL_ORGANIZATIONS,
        NULL AS OWNERSHIP_TYPE,
        NULL AS RANK_WITHIN_SECTOR
    FROM 
        BuildingDetails
    GROUP BY

),
GrandTotal AS (

        'Grand Total' AS CAMPUS_SECTOR,
        NULL AS BUILDING_NAME_LONG,
        NULL AS CITY,
        NULL AS STATE,
        SUM(TOTAL_FLOORS) AS TOTAL_FLOORS,
        SUM(TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA) AS TOTAL_ASSIGNABLE_AREA,
        NULL AS NUM_OF_ROOMS,
        NULL AS TOTAL_ORGANIZATIONS,
        NULL AS OWNERSHIP_TYPE,
        NULL AS RANK_WITHIN_SECTOR
    FROM 
        BuildingDetails
)

ORDER BY
